<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6623&amp;p=64538#p64538"><![CDATA[
Well here is the <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/downloads/trace-f.jpg" class="postlink">front</a> and <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/downloads/trace-b.jpg" class="postlink">back</a> of a CNROM compatible board. Not particularly interested in the results of this one, but it happened to be laying around and should be easy to verify pinouts. <br /><br />Scanned at 1200dpi, which seems sufficient, traces are 8+ pixels wide at that rez. This may prove to be harder than I thought, the traces aren't as distinct from the background as I thought, so trying to trace by chasing colors in a certain tolerance level probably won't work well. Working with the red channel only seems to give the most distinction between the traces and rest of the board.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=158">BootGod</a> — Tue Jul 20, 2010 5:42 pm</p><hr />
